'''Yanagimoto Ōtsuka Kofun''' (柳本大塚古墳) is a {{ill|kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in Tenri City, Nara Prefecture, Japan. It is part of the {{ill|Yanagimoto Kofun Cluster|ja|柳本古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, just north of the [[Makimuku ruins]]
== Overview ==
* '''location''': Yanagimoto Town, Tenri City, Nara Prefecture * '''Buried individual''': Unknown * '''built''': Early Kofun period * '''Kofun type''': Keyhole-shaped tumulus. The rear mound is not a perfect circle, and the front portion curves gently without flaring outward. The moat surrounding the mound is unconfirmed on the western side. * '''area''': Total length of approximately 94 meters; rear mound diameter of 54 meters.
The burial facility consists of a vertical stone chamber aligned along the north-south axis of the central rear mound. Within the chamber was a logboat-style hollowed wooden coffin measuring approximately 2 meters in length and 1.2 meters in width. burial goods such as bronze arrowheads and iron tools were discovered inside the coffin.
A secondary, irregularly shaped circular stone chamber with a diameter of 1 meter was also found. This chamber contained a {{ill|Large flower mirror|ja|大型内行花文鏡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, measuring 39.7 cm in diameter. The chamber featured a gabled roof structure with protruding ceiling stones and likely served as an auxiliary chamber for burial goods. The emphasis on the mirror, buried alone, suggests its special significance.
== burial goods ==
* '''Large Naiko Kamon Mirror''': ** Material: Bronze ** Diameter: 39.7 cm ** Design: Features quadrilobe and linked-arc motifs interspersed with thundercloud patterns. Surrounding these motifs are bead-shaped patterns densely arranged to fill the spaces. This mirror is currently held in the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|qq=draft|qq=draft}} collection. * '''Bronze arrowheads''': Six pieces * '''Iron fragments''': Various small pieces <gallery widths="200" heights="200"> File:Large domestic mirror, Kofun period, 300s-400s AD, bronze - Tokyo National Museum - Ueno Park, Tokyo, Japan - DSC09133.jpg|alt=Large Naiko Kamon Mirror|Large Naiko Kamon Mirror <gallery widths="200" heights="200"> File:Naikoukamon-kyo Tokyo National Museum.jpg|A [[flower mirror]] unearthed from the Kofun on display at [[Tokyo National Museum]] </gallery> == See Also == * [[List of kofun in Japan]]
